  "title": "Smart defaults in abandoned cart flows, with AI",
  "summary": "Does reducing friction in abandon cart flow setup increase setup and sending?",
  "slug": "smart-defaults-in-abandoned-cart-flows-with-ai",
  "product_area": "Flows",
  "test_topic": "Text adoption",
  "hypothesis": "<p>We believe that automating the addition and configuration of the text message action in an account's existing abandoned checkout email flow for companies that have at least 1 existing abandoned checkout email that has recovered at least $1500 in revenue over the last quarter will lead to increased SMS sending because of the reduced friction from automatically selecting and placing the text message action in a best practice position. </p><p>We will measure success using new 7D and new 28D SMS sends, and monitor new 7D and 28D SMS flows to ensure no negative impact.</p>",
